Files:
- platform/browser-extension/src/side-panel/components/PluginList.stories.tsx (add three stories)

Context:
PluginList uses `chrome.storage.session` for accordion state persistence (line 122). In Storybook, `chrome` is not available — the existing stories work because the effect catches the error and falls through. The `accordionHydrated` gate (line 196) returns null until hydrated, but the catch handler on line 131 sets it to true.

PluginList props (lines 82-102):
```tsx
plugins: PluginState[];
failedPlugins: FailedPluginState[];
activeTools: Set<string>;
setPlugins: Dispatch<SetStateAction<PluginState[]>>;
toolFilter: string;
onUpdate?: (pluginName: string) => void;
onRemove?: (pluginName: string) => void;
removingPlugins?: Set<string>;
pluginErrors?: Map<string, string>;
```

When `plugins=[]` and `failedPlugins=[]` and `toolFilter=""`, the component renders nothing (no empty state message — the empty state only shows when filtering with no matches). So the Empty story should show that the component renders nothing, which is still useful to document.

Actually, looking at the code more carefully: when `filterLower` is empty and both groups are empty, it renders the `<>` fragment with empty accordion sections — effectively nothing visible. This is correct behavior (browser tools card handles the "always has content" case). The story documents this edge case.

For `pluginErrors`, PluginList passes errors to PluginCard via `actionError={pluginErrors?.get(plugin.name) ?? null}` (line 223).

For `removingPlugins`, PluginList passes to PluginCard via `removingPlugin={removingPlugins?.has(plugin.name)}` (line 222).

Changes:
1. Add `Empty` story: `plugins=[]`, `failedPlugins=[]`, `toolFilter=""`. This renders an empty div — add a wrapper label explaining this is the expected behavior.

2. Add `WithPluginErrors` story: use mockPlugins, pass `pluginErrors={new Map([['slack', 'Failed to remove plugin: permission denied']])}` and `onUpdate`/`onRemove` callbacks.

3. Add `WithRemovingPlugin` story: use mockPlugins, pass `removingPlugins={new Set(['github'])}` and `onUpdate`/`onRemove` callbacks.

Constraints:
- Follow existing Demo pattern with useState for plugins
- Use the existing `mockPlugin` and `mockPlugins` from the file
- Do NOT modify PluginList.tsx

