- Follow existing Demo pattern
- Use existing mockNpmResult helper
- Add to the exports at the bottom

Files:
- platform/browser-extension/src/side-panel/components/ConfirmationDialog.stories.tsx (add three stories)

Context:
ConfirmationDialog (lines 26-119 of ConfirmationDialog.tsx) manages:
- `currentIndex` state for navigating between multiple confirmations
- `alwaysAllow` state toggled by a Switch component
- `handleAllow` calls `onRespond(current.id, 'allow', alwaysAllow || undefined)` (line 36)
- `handleDeny` calls `onRespond(current.id, 'deny')` (line 42)
- prev/next buttons appear when `count > 1` (lines 91-108)

The existing `SingleConfirmation` story has a play test that clicks Allow. We need three new interaction stories.

Changes:

1. `DenyInteraction` story:
```tsx
const DenyInteraction: Story = {
  args: {
    confirmations: [mockConfirmation()],
  },
  play: async ({ args }) => {
    const dialog = await screen.findByRole('dialog');
    const canvas = within(dialog);
    const denyBtn = canvas.getByRole('button', { name: /deny/i });
    await userEvent.click(denyBtn);
    await expect(args.onRespond).toHaveBeenCalledWith('conf-1', 'deny');
  },
};
```

2. `AlwaysAllowInteraction` story:
The Switch has `aria-label="Always allow this tool"`. Click the switch, then click Allow:
```tsx
const AlwaysAllowInteraction: Story = {
  args: {
    confirmations: [mockConfirmation()],
  },
  play: async ({ args }) => {
    const dialog = await screen.findByRole('dialog');
    const canvas = within(dialog);
    const switchEl = canvas.getByRole('switch', { name: /always allow/i });
    await userEvent.click(switchEl);
    const allowBtn = canvas.getByRole('button', { name: /^allow$/i });
    await userEvent.click(allowBtn);
    await expect(args.onRespond).toHaveBeenCalledWith('conf-1', 'allow', true);
  },
};
```

3. `NavigateConfirmations` story:
Uses 3 confirmations. prev/next are plain `<button>` elements with text "prev" and "next":
```tsx
const NavigateConfirmations: Story = {
  args: {
    confirmations: [
      mockConfirmation({ id: 'conf-1', tool: 'send_message', plugin: 'slack' }),
      mockConfirmation({ id: 'conf-2', tool: 'create_issue', plugin: 'github', params: { title: 'Bug' } }),
      mockConfirmation({ id: 'conf-3', tool: 'screenshot', plugin: 'browser' }),
    ],
  },
  play: async ({ canvasElement }) => {
    const dialog = await screen.findByRole('dialog');
    const canvas = within(dialog);
    // Initially shows "1 of 3"
    await expect(canvas.getByText('1 of 3')).toBeVisible();
    // Click next
    await userEvent.click(canvas.getByText('next'));
    await expect(canvas.getByText('2 of 3')).toBeVisible();
    // Click prev
    await userEvent.click(canvas.getByText('prev'));
    await expect(canvas.getByText('1 of 3')).toBeVisible();
  },
};
```

Note: The "1 of 3" counter is rendered as separate spans: `{safeIndex + 1} of {count}` inside a single `<span className="font-mono text-xs">`. The text content will be "1 of 3" as a single text node.

Constraints:
- Import `fn` from 'storybook/test' (already imported in the file)
- The meta already has `args: { onRespond: fn() }` so each story inherits it
- Add all three to the exports at the bottom
- Do NOT modify ConfirmationDialog.tsx
